	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=67336><span id= >Benzoate</span></a><br><span id=notbold>51 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>OK, here's a bit of advice on how to take them both.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have spent a lot of time soloing the King and High Shammy, from levels 26 - 28.  The key is to stay in the far back right corner as you face the throne.  the King will run directly to you with no adds this way.  Also, for some reason the Howlers in the room dont seem to like his pet and will kill it for you. :)<br><br>Killed him probably 40+ times, got a ton of Cold Iron, the crown once, the Naginata once, and a ton of junk.  If the duo is too hard for you at this level, try rooting the king to open the fight.  draw the shammy to you, and root him in the right corner.  After that, you can run back across the wall to the left corner to nuke the king to death.  Doing it this way spreads the 2 high end mobs far enough apart that the shammy can't heal the king.  kill him, loot up, and head for Paineel.  I would do this a lot to stagger the spawns apart.  Each has a 1hr 10min cycle or there abouts.  Hope this helps.</p>&nbsp;<br>Venger<br>Dread Lord of Innoruuk<br>&lt;Mystical Lightfighters&gt;<br>Morell Thule</td></tr>
